d plastic clip that snaps onto the chair support in a couple of seconds.";i:35;s:101:"Push off or cut off with a dremel tool any decorative or nonfunctioning collars around the seat post.";i:36;s:113:"Place the base back on the seat post temporarily so it seats fully and mark the top of the base on the seat post.";i:37;s:69:"Set the base aside and measure from the mark to the base of the seat.";i:38;s:55:"WikiHow Quick Video on How to Fix a Sinking Desk Chair.";i:39;s:149:"To fix a sinking desk chair start by sliding the plastic cylinder on the extendable part of the chair up or down so you can see the metal underneath.";i:40;s:102:"Then set the chair to your preferred height laying it on its side if you need to so it stays in place.";i:41;s:82:"Once the chair is at the right height wrap a hose clamp around the metal cylinder.";i:42;s:106:"Office chairs can sink any time the cylinder fails whether you bought it a month ago or spent years on it.";i:43;s:102:"Below I help you determine how to fix a sinking office chair in four detailed easy-to-understand ways.";i:44;s:72:"Your office chair is sinking because of fluid leakage from the cylinder.";i:45;s:54:"A pneumatic office chair has a single-acting cylinder.";i:46;s:47:"This is a spring that has been filled with air.";i:47;s:114:"When the piston is moved further out of the chamber the air inside the chamber expands allowing the seat to lower.";i:48;s:78:"If your chair keeps sinking this means that the cylinder is no longer working.";i:49;s:41:"How to stop an office chair from sinking.";i:50;s:46:"Fixing a sinking desk chair is not a hard job.";i:51;s:78:"Here we put the right information on how you fix a sinking desk chair at home.";i:52;s:57:"Well-designed office chairs are meant to be long-lasting.";i:53;s:117:"However as durable as they are they may fall into a state of disrepair that makes them uncomfortable and even unsafe.";i:54;s:29:"How to fix your office chair.";i:55;s:71:"There are two methods you can use when it comes to fixing this problem.";i:56;s:90:"You might have to root around your garage or take a trip to a DIY store for the key tools.";i:57;s:76:"Firstly you can use a hose clamp to prevent the chairs cylinder from moving.";i:58;s:74:"Secondly you can use PVC pipe to also stop the cylinder from sliding down.";i:59;s:114:"Knowing how to fix a sinking office chair can help avoid health issues besides saving money on buying a new chair.";i:60;s:82:"If your faulty office chair is too old fixing it may just be a temporary solution.";i:61;s:59:"It is likely to develop another problem in the near future.";}}